http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Centre%E2%80%99s-view-is-Belagavi-Nippani-are-part-of-State%E2%80%99/article14009044.ece

Referring to the border dispute between Maharashtra and Karnataka, Union Minister for Chemicals and Fertilizers H.N. Ananth Kumar has said that Union government’s view was that Belagavi, Nippani and Karwar were part of Karnataka and they would continue to be with the State.Also, he said that Maharashtra Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis should desist from creating confusion by issuing statements on sensitive subjects such as the boundary dispute having a potential to harm linguistic harmony and peace in the two States.Addressing a large gathering at the Bharatiya Janata Party’s Vijay Sankalp Samavesh and virtually launching the party’s campaign for the zilla and taluk panchayat elections here on Tuesday, he said that he would speak to Mr. Fadnavis in the matter.He said unified Karnataka had come about after a long struggle.Even the Mahajan Commission submitted its report only after both Maharashtra and Karnataka agreed to abide by its report, which had made clear the status of Belagavi, Nippani, Karwar and other towns and villages.Even the Union government is of the view that these areas are integral part of the State.“It is not proper if people held a different points of view on the report now,” he added.Maharashtra Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis told to desist from creating confusionSensitive issues like boundary limits have the potential to harm linguistic harmony: MPAnanth Kumar says he will speak to Maharashtra Chief Minister on the matter